BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260628T121623Z
UID:TS1-7C637520-3FDB-4D34-821F-04CA4BA99916
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261008
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261009
SUMMARY:Request estate account transcript (Form 4506-T) — check for TC 421 
 <2026-10-08 Thu>
DESCRIPTION:Brenda's Form 706 was mailed by Haislet's office 2026-04-08.  I
 RS says\nwait 6 months after filing before requesting an account transcrip
 t.\nTC 421 on the transcript = return accepted as filed / exam complete\n(
 functional equivalent of the closing letter\, which is no longer sent\naut
 omatically).  If no TC 421 yet\, check again later. Closing letter\n(optio
 nal\, $67 via Pay.gov) can be requested 9 months after filing\n(~Jan 2027)
  or any time once TC 421 appears.\n\nCan do this myself (signed the 706 as
  executor — no need to involve\nHaislet): Form 4506-T: <https://www.irs.go
 v/pub/irs-pdf/f4506t.pdf>\n• Line 1a: Estate of Brenda A. Webster\n• Line 
 1b: Brenda's SSN (NOT the estate EIN — 706 account is keyed to\n  decedent
  SSN)\n• Line 3: my name\, title "Executor"\, address — must match what's 
 on\n  the filed 706\n• Line 6: 706\, check box 6b (Account Transcript) — o
 nly valid option\n  for estate tax\n• Line 9: period = date-of-death year-
 end\n• Check attestation box\, sign\, date\, Title line = "Executor" (else
 \n  rejected)\n• Send to Ogden UT RAIVS team (CA domicile) — fax faster th
 an mail\,\n  use fax number from the chart in the current form's instructi
 ons\n• Transcript arrives by mail in a few weeks\; look for TC 421 in\n  t
 ransaction list\nPhone status check: IRS estate & gift tax line 866-699-40
 83 Ref:\n<https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/tr
 anscripts-in-lieu-of-estate-tax-closing-letters>
CATEGORIES:cal,estate,org-calendar-staging
END:VEVENT
